&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Appearance Property: &lt;/strong&gt;He has silver armor as aluminum is a silvery colour. He also has blue eyes and white hair as there are hints of blue and white present in the colour of aluminum. He also has thirteen freckles because that is the amount of electrons aluminum has which was obtained through his atomic&nbsp;number&nbsp;and has 13 electrons revolving around the nucleus. He is also skinny as he weighs 26.98kg (his atomic mass is 26.98). He also has an extremely thin layer of aluminum oxide around his body in order to protect him from corrosion.&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Behaviour Property: &lt;/strong&gt;Captain Al is very clumsy as he is highly reactive as he wants to lose his three electrons thus being clumsy as he is always losing electrons. He is highly reactive and clumsy when he reacts with acids, water and alkali&#039;s such as Sodium Hydroxide. He is also friendly as he forms lots of alloys with metals such as copper. He forms alloys to get stronger thus being able to make lots of friends and forming these friendships easily. These friendships make him a stronger person overall.&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Super Power Property: &lt;/strong&gt;His main super power is he is able to transform his body into thin&nbsp;sheets which will allow him to fit into extremely small spaces that a person usually cannot fit in. This occurs&nbsp;as aluminum is highly ductile (able to be beaten into extremely thins sheets). Once he fits into the tiny spaces, his body regains its normal form. His second super power is that he is able to transform his armor from a dull silver to a shiny silver as aluminum is shiny. This allows him to blind his enemies temporarily for 10&nbsp;seconds and this allows him battle his enemy with worrying about sustaining damage.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

