&lt;p&gt;Super Villain: Krazy Flamer (Based on Potassium)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(I really can&#039;t draw to save my life sorry)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Appearance&lt;/strong&gt;: Armour is a silver/grey colour because potassium exists as such and turns into a dull grey when exposed to oxygen. The lilac colour on her appearance represents the potassium when it is reacting with water which she uses to her advantage. Potassium can be easily cut with a knife or scalpel which is why she wears a belt &ndash; this belt, with the push of the button in the center, acts as a force field to protect her from her enemies.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Behaviour: &lt;/strong&gt;Due to its reputation in the food industry as a healthy substance, she is able to be trusted by those around her and is able to mingle in society. She does, however, have to be quite careful because the melting point of potassium is quite low (63.5 degrees Celsius) that the heat from a candle could melt it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Super Villain Ability: &lt;/strong&gt;The bracelets on her wrists contain water which she can easily access in order to create flames. The hydrogen within the water reacts violently with the potassium and creates a lilac flame which could potentially explode. She uses this reaction to wreak havoc amongst the town and is very destructive when left to her own devices. She sets fires within the towns and then the gases which contain potassium released from the fire get into the people&rsquo;s bloodstream which can be harmful to a person and potentially life threatening.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Lithman&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Appearance: Lithman&#039;s silvery-white is&nbsp;a representation of the true colours of Lithium. His armour that he wears to protect himself from harm from all villains is a metallic luster, which is the colour that derives from cutting open lithium.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Behaviour: because of Lithium being considered highly flammable, I have decide to make my superhero an extremely angry individual, essentially known as a hot head, who gets heated throughout discussions with super-villans.&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Superpower: Lithium is known to be a great conductor of electricity. My superhero has the ability to conduct electricity from miles away. He helps cities in need, and provide them with energy that is essential for their own survival. Lithium is also considered to be extremely flammable. Not only can he provide electricity, but he can create fires at any given moment, to provide himself warmth and protection from those whom are feared.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Super power:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Skeletium can control the composition of his strontium bones. He can modify the percentage of isotopes that compose him and use his properties to fight crime. Much like another&nbsp;superhero, Skeletium has the power to regenerate himself as a result of his ability to both cause and cure bone cancer with his 90Sr and 89Sr isotopes. He can also react with other elements to his advantage, as he his pretty smart.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Appearance:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Skeletium is a skeleton with black bones. The colour results from strontium&#039;s reaction with oxygen. His armour is of a yellowish tone which ironically represents the natural appearance of the element. Skeletium carries a bow and arrows that are made out of his own bones. He also has a pet naked mole-rat, as the animal is immune to cancer and thus, can always be by his side.&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Behavior:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Skeletium is a&nbsp;nice guy, but he is extremely short-tempered. He is known for overreacting to pretty much everything. On the other hand,&nbsp;he&nbsp;is very charitable and is often seen in hospitals curing patients. He never refuses to give a hand to anybody but he makes it clear that he does not want to receive anything in return. When fighting criminals, Skeletium is ruthless. Due to the properties of his main weapon, 90Sr, (and his temper) his interventions are often quite cruel and have caused numerous controversies. Deep-inside, he despises all humans, as he is often criticized for his actions and also for the fact that most people stay far away from him, fearing that they will be contaminated. His only true friend is his pet mole-rat, which&nbsp;helps him calm down when he is frustrated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;*Naked mole-rats can very rarely suffer from the disease, but are usually deemed as immune.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;2- Drawing + properties&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Name of my character: Lucidum&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Property 1 : Appearance&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lucidum is a shiny solid and has some grey areas on its body, just like arsenic, who&#039;s stable form is silver/gray, brittle and solid.&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Arsenic does not melt when it&#039;s heated, it actually goes through sublimation (solid to gas), which is why I made the hair of Lucidum look like a flame, and not flat against her back. I left some parts of it white because the gas produced after sublimation can be seen as a white cloud (hence the white parts).&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Around her waist, is 33 little balls, representing the 33 protons or the atomic number of arsenic (As).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Property 2 : Behaviour&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lucidum is the contrary of solitary. Because of her very shiny body, it attracts a lot of people. People are quite confused, because most of the time they think of Arsenic as poison, so when they see how odorless and shiny it looks, they let their guards down.&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Property 3 : Superpower&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One of its superpowers is that Lucidum is very poisonous and toxic, just like arsenic (As) and its compounds (which was commonly known as the King of poison). Indeed, being exposed for a too long period of time to it could give you cancer, brain conditions, and cause many other effects. Lucidum uses its shininess and physique&nbsp;to attract people and then expose&nbsp;them to her toxicity.&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;sources :&nbsp;https://www.lenntech.fr/data-perio/as.htm&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

