&lt;p&gt;https://www.thoughtco.com/arsenic-element-facts-606500&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Appearance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;: &lt;/strong&gt;He has bright red hair because calcium burns quite vigorously in oxygen. Calcium exposed to oxygen creates a brick red flame, so his hair is like a bright red flame. He also has really shiny teeth that are almost blinding. Since calcium reacts to oxygen like a bright fire, when his teeth are exposed, his teeth shine super brightly.&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Behavior:&nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;He is really energetic and moves a lot. Calcium exposed to oxygen creates a brick of fire, and fire is always in motion, so he is also always in motion. But exposed to water, he becomes gloomy and sad. Calcium reacts very slowly to water.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Superpower: He can create fire. With oxygen everywhere, he can create fire when he wants anywhere he wants. His fire can also blind for a second, because the second the fire is formed, there is a bright light. His bones are also his weapons. Calcium strengthen bones so all of his bones can be used as weapons such as swords and shields.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Appearance:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Miss H is the smallest superhero, (hydrogen element, made of only one proton and electron). She is also invisible and nearly undetectable to her enemies, as hydrogen is an odorless, tasteless, colorless gas.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Behaviour:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;She hates to be alone and always seeks to bond with someone else. She often sticks close to members of her own family (hydrogen is diatomic), but can also make friends with others quite easily.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Super Power:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;She has fire powers because hydrogen gas is highly flammable. Since she is hard to detect she can easily enter her enemies&rsquo; hideouts and lairs unseen and burn them down. She also has the ability to create a massive nuclear explosion (H-bomb), however, this power can only be used once as it would cost her her life.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Carat Compressor&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Appearance: Carat&#039;s shiny golden hair and suit match the color of gold in it&#039;s solid form. Gold is also seen as a very valuable material, that is often a symbol of wealth. As such, Carat dresses like someone who is living a very wealthy life style. He has an over the top golden suit, with nice shoes and many rings on his hands. It also matches his day job, which is as a profitable business man.&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Behavior: Despite his attention grabbing appearance, Carat is someone who prefers to be alone and work alone, he only lets few into his personal life. This is based on the fact that gold is a practically non reactive substance, only reacting with halogens and a mixture of hydrochloric and nitric acid, know as aqua regia. Yet, to the public, he has an air of grandeur and acts as though he is an extremely important person, once again going off how gold is viewed by modern society,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Super Power: Gold is known to be the most malleable and ductile of metals, so Carat&#039;s power directly reflects that. With more gold in his body than the average human, Carat is capable of making his body incredibly flat and stretching it out to great lengths. He uses this power to get into places that people normally would not be allowed into. He most often uses this power to rob from banks and add onto his existing wealth. His only real weakness is, like the chemical gold, he is very soft and a well placed bullet or stab through his body could be deadly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Super Villain: The Mad Merc&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Superpower properties&lt;/strong&gt;: The Mad Merc&rsquo;s super villain powers are to be able to shape shift into a liquid mental, or solidify into an object. At standard room temperature and pressure mercury becomes a liquid. Melting/freezing point is around -40 degrees Celsius. He is able to duplicate himself as he can become a liquid which benefits him during battle. When in a non-metallic form The Mad Merc is able to shot poisonous mercury gas rays from his eyes. This is possible due to the rays heating up the mercury in his system which is already in a liquid form and turns it into mercury gas which is extremely toxic when inhaled and can cause death. Boiling point is approximately 360 degrees Celsius.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Behaviour properties:&lt;/strong&gt; The Mad Merc is typically a loner due to his extremely heavy density which is approximately 5.427g/cm which tends to shake or vibrate the objects around him while he walks giving an intimidating characteristic which scares people away. The Mad Merc tends to be more on the cold side due to the fact that mercury is a poor conductor of heat which makes him almost unapproachable. In addition, the Mad Merc when in contact with others can send little electrical shocks to the other individuals because mercury is a very good conductor of electricity.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Appearance properties:&lt;/strong&gt; The Mad Merc&rsquo;s skin is not made out of tissue rather it is composed of malleable metal substance. This is due to the fact that Mad Merc&rsquo;s body is inorganic meaning he does not consist of living matter. This contributes to his exterior body being the shiny colour of silver when he is in any form. The Mad Merc&rsquo;s body colour is also based on mercury being known as quicksilver which is seen with its former name being &ldquo;hydragyrum&rdquo; which refers to the Greek words &ldquo;hydro&rdquo; meaning water and &ldquo;argyros&rdquo; meaning sliver. &nbsp;Mercury can be found most commonly as cinnabar (mercuric sulfide). The red pigment vermilion is obtained by grinding natural cinnabar or synthetic mercuric sulfide. The Mad Merc&rsquo;s eye colour would be red due to the presences of mercury sulfide dust that was blown into his eyes, completely deforming them to be all red. There is also the presence of mercury sulfide in his belt. The Mad Merc doesn&rsquo;t need a custom as he is turning from an extremely hard solid which is when he appears more bulky (rock like appearance), to a liquid which is when he is a substance which can take any form. The one article he wears is his temperature regulating belt which allows him to decide which phase (solid or liquid) he wants to take the form of by pushing on of the two buttons by raising or lowering the heat. Underneath the logo Mad Merc is the number 80 which represent the atomic number of mercury.&lt;/p&gt;

