&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Name of character&lt;/strong&gt;: Lady Chloros&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Appearance:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;She has yellow-green hair and eyes, representing the colour of chlorine in its gaseous state. She also wears an amber-coloured bodysuit, representing the colour of chlorine in its liquid state.&nbsp;Her bodysuit, gloves and boots are all made of shiny rubber. The rubber is shiny because it&#039;s been chlorinated, in other words, it&#039;s been treated with a chlorine solution.&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Behaviour:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lady Chloros is a clean freak. She hates germs and bacteria and she goes out of her way to clean surfaces before coming into contact with them, mimicking the disinfecting property of hypochlorous acid (HClO). She loves wearing chlorinated rubber because another benefit of having rubber treated with chlorine is that it also makes the rubber resistant to staining. Lady Chloros detests stains because it makes her feel dirty.&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Superpower:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lady Chloros is able to, on command, breathe out chlorine gas. She can also control where the gas goes. Her preferred method is to send the gas to her opponent&#039;s lungs, thus making her opponent have a hard time breathing. As they lay on the ground choking, she then knocks them out. When chlorine gas comes into contact with the moist tissues in the lungs, an acid is produced and it damages the tissues.&lt;/p&gt;

