&lt;p&gt;1. &lt;strong&gt;The Reaction of Aluminum with Hydrochloric Acid:&lt;/strong&gt;&nbsp;Captain Al will react with diluted hydrochloric acid. If he drinks water that contains hydrochloric acid in it, hydrogen gas will be produced inside his stomach. This causes him to start burping so that he can get the Hydrogen gas released from his body. As a result, he will turn his attention toward releasing the hydrogen gas from his body so he will be easy to attack. This reaction can destroy his protective oxide layer which is why he is focused on releasing this gas from his body. The chemical formula for this reaction is as follows: 2Al(solid) + 6HCl(aqueous) ----&amp;gt; 2AlCl3(aqueous)&nbsp;+ 3H2 (gas).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. &lt;strong&gt;The Reaction of Aluminum with Water:&lt;/strong&gt;Aluminum reacts with water. When his protective oxide layer is damaged, he is exposed to attacks including water thus he will react with water. This reaction will decrease Captain Al&#039;s strength until another oxide layer is regenerated. His strength decreases because when aluminum reacts with water, it lowers the strength of the metal.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3. T&lt;strong&gt;he Reaction of Aluminum with Oxygen:&lt;/strong&gt;&nbsp;When Captain Al lowers his oxide layer in order to manipulate electricity or when his oxide layer is damaged, he will react with oxygen. This reaction will cause him to begin the corrosion process. As a result, his movements will slow down as well as his attacks thus his strikes will be ineffective as the enemy can block his attacks since they are slow.&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;4. &lt;strong&gt;The reaction of Aluminum and Iodine:&lt;/strong&gt;&nbsp;Captain Al likes to carry aluminum powder with him in case of an emergency. This powdered Aluminum will react with Iodine. When he the powder comes into contact with iodine, he will add water to catalyse this reaction. As a result, this reaction produces a cloud of purple vapour/smoke thus allowing him to escape.&lt;/p&gt;

