&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chemical Reactions Involving Chlorine:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. Chlorine and Hydrogen (HCl)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These two elements together can form hydrogen chloride gas at room temperature. When this gas is inhaled, it can burn a person&rsquo;s respiratory tract and cause them to cough and choke. Lady Chloros can manipulate this gas and use it to incapacitate her enemies. Also, when HCl is dissolved in water, it forms hydrochloric acid. Lady Chloros can use this corrosive acid to burn her enemies&rsquo; skin.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2. Chlorine and Carbon (CCl4)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These two elements together can form carbon tetrachloride. It&rsquo;s a colourless liquid that evaporates fast and thus is found mostly in its gas form in the environment. When inhaled, this compound can cause liver and kidney failure. Also, if a person was exposed to high concentrations of this compound, immediate effects include headaches, dizziness and sleepiness. Lady Chloros can use high levels of carbon tetrachloride to disorient her enemies by making them have headaches and dizziness and then defeat them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3. Chlorine and Methane (CHCl3)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These two elements can combine to form chloroform, a colourless, sweet-smelling and dense liquid. When chloroform is inhaled, it can knock out or daze a person. However, chloroform evaporates quickly so it must be administered fast. Lady Chloros uses this liquid in close combat. When she is near her opponent, she soaks one of the rags that she always carries with her to disinfect surfaces, with chloroform and chokes her opponent with it, ensuring that they inhale it and pass out.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4. Chlorine and Phosphorus (PCl3)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These two elements can combine and form phosphorus trichloride, a colourless liquid that is highly corrosive and toxic. When a person comes into contact with the compound, it can severely irritate and burn the skin and the eyes. Lady Chloros uses this liquid to burn and severely harm her opponents, impairing their ability to fight.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;P.S. The numbers in the chemical formulas should be subscripts&lt;/p&gt;

