&lt;p&gt;Chemical Reactions&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) Tungsten hexafluoride (WF6)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tungsten hexafluoride is an extremely corrosive compound. When humans are exposed, their eyes and respiratory system are affected first. It makes them lose vision and cough. Once it mixes with fluids from the body, it acts as an acid and burns skin. Prolonged exposure can be fatal. Wolfram can use this compound to deter his enemies.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) Tungsten carbide (WC)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tungsten carbide is its most basic form is a grey powder. It can pressed and formed into many different objects. It is very resistant to heat and is also very hard, which means that it could be useful when it comes to making armour to protect himself.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3) Tungsten hexachloride (WCl6)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tungsten hexachloride is prepared by chlorinating tungsten is a sealed container at 600 degrees Celsius. This could be possible to do for Wolfram since he is resistant to heat. Tungsten hexachloride is an aggressively corrosive oxidant, which can be used to disable an enemy&#039;s weapon.&lt;/p&gt;

