&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Appearance&lt;/strong&gt;&nbsp;property: Iodite&rsquo;s costume is made from 100% solid iodine; consequently, it has a gray, shiny, glowing color. Also, Iodite has purple hair; when she uses her super power, she can blend in and not be recognised by others around her.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Behavior&lt;/strong&gt;&nbsp;property: Due to the strong and unpleasant smell of solid iodine from the costume she wears, that has impregnated in her skin, Iodite tends to stay away from others when at work and to spend most of her time alone.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Super power&lt;/strong&gt;&nbsp;property: Iodite has enhanced regenerative capabilities due to the large amount of iodine in her body; iodine works as a sterilizer for her to recover from outer wounds on her body. Also, her most lethal super power is her ability to create a purple toxic gas; when solid iodine is heated, it turns into a purple gas that is very harmful.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;By looking at the following picture, we recognize some of Iodite&#039;s properties:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Her purple hair&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Her 100% solid iodine costume, that is gray and shinny (the stars on suit represent glow)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The purple gas around her that is iodine&nbsp;gas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3 different chemical reactions involving that atom&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nitrogen Triiodide:&lt;/strong&gt;&nbsp;When 3 atoms of iodine react with 1 atom of nitrogen, it creates nitrogen triiodide. Nitrogen triiodide is a form of explosive that is very sensitive, it can be detonated by the snap of a finger or the vibration of a footstep. The reaction between iodine and nitrogen is as follow: I + N = NI(small 3).&nbsp;To find nitrogen, Iodite will simply take any of her home cleaning furniture as they contain ammonia in it (ammonia contains a lot of nitrogen). Iodite will then be able to create bombs from nitrogen triiodide and attack her enemies with them from a long distance.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Potassium Iodide:&lt;/strong&gt;&nbsp;When 1 atom of iodine reacts with 1 atom of potassium, it creates potassium iodide. Potassium iodide is a medication used to protect the immune system from radiation exposure. In a large quantity, potassium iodine is very dangerous, it can lead to allergic reactions, vomiting, diarrhea, rashes, and swelling of specific glands in the body. The reaction between iodine and potassium is as follow: I + K = KI.&nbsp;Because potassium is so reactive, it is not present free in nature, Iodite will need to find minerals such as sylvite (KCl) in lakes (sylvite contain a lot of potassium). Once she does, she will be able to infect her enemies to slow them down or even kill them if they are given a lethal doze.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Iodine Pentafluoride:&lt;/strong&gt;&nbsp;When 1 atom of iodine reacts with 5 atoms of fluorine, it creates iodine pentafluoride. Iodine pentafluoride is a yellow liquid, that reacts with water to make hydrofluoric acid (HF); a very dangerous acid that can kill you when in contact with your skin. The reaction between iodine and fluorine is as follow: I + F = IF(small 5).&nbsp;Fluorine is found in rocket fuel, which will be hard to find for Iodite. Consequently, she will use fluorine from refrigeration fluids such as Freon as her source; These are fluids used by refrigerator to cool down, which have a lot of fluorine. Iodite will be able to form iodine pentafluoride, put it in water, and form hydrofluoric acid to attack her enemies from a close distance&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Chemical Reactions:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;1. Hydrogen and Sulphur (H2S)&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This chemical compound forms hydrogen sulfide which is a colourless gas that smells like rotten eggs. It is poisonous, corrosive and flammable. Although it&rsquo;s smell is pungent at first, it deadens the sense of smell, so enemies may not be aware of it until it is too late. Miss H can control the amount of the gas produced. Low-level exposure can lead to fatigue, headaches, poor memory, and more, so she would use low dosages to incapacitate victims, but not to kill. High-level exposure can lead to immediate collapse, loss of breath and death. High-level exposure would be used for immediate and lethal results&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;2. Hydrogen and Chlorine (HCl)&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This chemical compound forms hydrochloric acid, which is corrosive. The concentration of the acid can be controlled. Very concentrated hydrochloric acid forms acidic mists. As a solution and as mist, hydrochloric acid has a corrosive effect on human tissue. Respiratory organs, eyes, skin, and intestines can be damaged irreversibly. This can be used to cause lasting damage to enemies.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;3. Hydrogen and Phosphorus (PH3)&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This compound forms a colourless flammable toxic gas. It can also form explosive mixtures with air and self-ignite. It is toxic and attacks the central nervous system. It can be absorbed by inhalation or through the skin. Overexposure can cause nausea, vomiting, abdominal pain, muscle pains, chills and more. Miss H can use this gas to debilitate her enemies.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3 Reactions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Cesium reacting with Oxygen:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When Cesium is exposed to the air and the moisture in it, it tarnishes very easily.&nbsp;As it tarnishes, it also begins to self combust, melting and reacting with Oxygen to create a rose/magenta coloured flame.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Cesium reacting with H2O:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When Cesium comes into contact with water, it creates an exothermic reaction. The Cesium hits the water and it reacts very quickly, creating what looks like a small explosion and a cloud of smoky vapor.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Cesium reacting&nbsp;with Fluorine:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cesium reacts strongly with all the halogens, like Fluorine for example. When Cesium and Fluorine come into contact, they react together and ignite. The flame creates an extremely bright, blinding light.&lt;/p&gt;

