&lt;p&gt;1)Tellurium reaction with air:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;when tellurium is heated in air it combusts into a green/blue flame at a temperature of 340 degrees Celsius. Tellus uses this power to form balls of tellurium in his palm and make them automatically combust. this allows him to shot fireballs at his enemies which burn them severely.&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) Tellurium reacts with Chlorine:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;when tellurium reacts with chlorine it creates a solid known as tellurium tetrachloride.&nbsp;Te + 2 Cl2 &rarr; TeCl4. This solid is extremely toxic and therefore Tellus is able to use this. he forms this substance on his fists so when he has to fight in hand to hand combat he delivers toxic blows to his enemies. this leaves his enemies burned and blind if he hits them close in the face.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3) Tellurium reacts with Sodium.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tellurium reacts with sodium and forms a substance known as sodium telluride (Na2 Te). this substance is an extremely unstable acid. Tellus can use this acid to melt through any defences or any materials for entrance to wherever he desires.&lt;/p&gt;

