&lt;p&gt;Another reaction involving aluminum:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;5) Reaction of Aluminum with Nitric Acid: When Captain Al comes into contact with nitric acid, it will react with it. This reaction will passivate Captain Al meaning it will make Captain Al less reactive while creating an extra oxide layer. This reaction will allow Captain Al to wear double the armor as another oxide layer is created on top of the existing one.&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

