&lt;p&gt;Superhero: Cobalto, CO for short&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Appearance: She has silver-grey hair like the colour of cobalt.&nbsp; Her hands are grey like a magnet. She wears fireproof suit as cobalt has a very high melting point.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Behavior: Cobalt is a brittle metal so she is tough but when something is very special to her then she has a very delicate temperament.&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Super power: She can control magnets and her hands are magnets because cobalt has magnetic properties. Since cobalt is a hard metal, she also has very hard skin that protects her when she is saving the world.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reactions:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With water Francium will cause a large explosion that would send radioactive material through the entire area surrounding. The Francium will turn into francium oxide and produce a dangerous hydrogen gas.&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With any Halogen, francium will also cause a large explosion of the same nature. Creating francium halides such as Francium Iodide.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With air it is expected that Francium will great Francium Super oxide (FO2) that other superoxides have been seen in the body&#039;s immune system to kill off other invading germs. It is assumed that this combination would be a toxin in the air.&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Chemical Reactions&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) The main use for cobalt is to alloy it with other metals such as aluminum or nickel which creates high-powered magnets. So, she gets along really well with her superhero buds Alumie (aluminum) and Nick (nickel) and when she teams up with them, she is even more powerful. She could defeat villains with teamwork.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2)&nbsp;The smelting process of cobalt can release arsenic vapors. So, when she gets too hot and her fire suit is no longer useful, she starts to sweat out arsenic vapors. This could happen on purpose, by trying to defeat the villain with the arsenic vapors or the villain could use this to make her accidentally poison civilians.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3)&nbsp;If Cobalto gets bombarded with neutrons in a nuclear reactor, she will become Co-60 and will then be able to detect flaws in metal.&lt;/p&gt;
